Edges:
Red/Green/Blue for edges correspond to generators

Vertices:
Red start vertedx is the identity
Black vetices project voraciously to the identity
Light blue vertices don't project to the identity

Walls:
Purple walls are ones not seperated from the identity by any other walls
Orange walls seperate one of the black vertices from the identity, but are not purple

They are drawn on the back of prints of the tilings taken from the wikipedia page for triangle groups
The image bleeding through was used to draw in walls as hyperbolic/euclidean lines
